{
  "stem": "11671.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you weren't allowed on the streets until, until 8:00 in the morning so--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we, we heard rumors that the Jews, Jews were being taken to camp, to labor camps.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my parents-- we never heard anything about Auschwitz or concentration or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, parents used to whisper to each other about things happening.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we children never heard any mention of that, just that the Jewish people, we should get our rucksacks together, because we don't know when we will be taken to camps to work.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father always said that, you know, not to worry about that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My sister even had an opportunity by a Romanian family to hide us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he said, we're not worried about going to camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Jewish people are not afraid of work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody has to suffer during the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Some people have to be soldiers and fight on the fronts, and some people have to work in factories, and we are not afraid to go to work.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we, we never heard-- definitely we heard people were being taken away by transport, but we never heard where or--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was, because we, we were, you know-- just from day to day, we didn't know when we were going to be taken away.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we prepared by having, like, a backpack and prepare, you know, some of our, our clothing that we could get to it fast.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we never, we never, you know-- we weren't scared every minute of the day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, into Hungary-- in the later years, when, when, the I guess-- we weren't taken-- Hungarian Jews were not taken until April of 1944.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
